否则  我们就会变成隔壁那鳄鱼的美食了

525
00:41:48,460 --> 00:41:50,420
Someone has to stop him.
必须有人制止这一切

526
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:58,300
Before you say anything, l'm here to save your necks.
在你开口之前  我生命我是来救你们的

527
00:41:58,470 --> 00:42:01,890
After putting them on the chopping block in the first place?
先把那些混蛋放上断头台

528
00:42:02,810 --> 00:42:07,310
Listen, you want your wife back as much as l want to go home to my family.
听着  你和我一样 渴望与家人重聚

529
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:11,060
You think there's another copy of Inkheart out there, let's find it together.
你觉得还有一本《墨水心》 我们就一起去找

530
00:42:11,230 --> 00:42:13,650
And how do you intend that we escape?
那你计划如何帮助我们逃脱

531
00:42:16,570 --> 00:42:18,070
Page 14.
第14页

532
00:42:19,820 --> 00:42:21,570
The mighty storm?
大暴风雨

533
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:25,290
Get in the castle! Let's go!
到城堡里去  走

534
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:28,790
"From the far north they heard a low wail of the wind...
在遥远的北方  传来了风的低呼声

535
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,960
...and Uncle Henry and Dorothy could see...
亨利叔叔和桃乐丝能看到

536
00:42:31,130 --> 00:42:34,130
...where the long grass bowed in waves before the coming storm.
在暴风来临之前  那些长长的草弯下腰

537
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:38,510
'There's a cyclone coming, Em. l'll go after the stock."'
有飓风要来了  我必须照顾一下牲口

538
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,050
Good doggies.
乖小狗

539
00:42:43,390 --> 00:42:44,930
"Suddenly, Uncle Henry stood up."
突然间  亨利叔叔站了起来

540
00:42:46,350 --> 00:42:48,140
Get out of the square!
快离开广场

541
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:51,770
"He ran toward the sheds where the cows and the horses were kept.
他朝着棚屋奔去 那里关着奶牛和马

542
00:42:51,940 --> 00:42:54,020
Aunt Em dropped her work and came to the door.
阿姨也放下手里的活  走到门口

543
00:42:54,190 --> 00:42:56,610
One glance told her of the danger close at hand.
只消一眼  她就知道  危险临近了

544
00:42:56,780 --> 00:42:58,900
'Quick, Dorothy! Run for the cellar!"'
快  桃乐丝  快到地下室

545
00:42:59,070 --> 00:43:00,490
There she is! Come on!
她在那  快追

546
00:43:00,660 --> 00:43:02,070
"A strange thing happened.
奇怪的事发生了

547
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:07,120
The house whirled around two or three times and rose slowly through the air.
房子旋转了一两圈 报纸和玫瑰在空中盘旋

548
00:43:08,710 --> 00:43:12,170
Dorothy felt as if she were going up in a balloon."
桃乐丝觉得自己  就像乘上了热气球

549
00:43:14,670 --> 00:43:15,800
That should do it!
这样就行了

550
00:43:19,470 --> 00:43:20,840
Let's get out of here!
我们走

551
00:43:25,510 --> 00:43:27,020
Must've run off!
一定是逃了

552
00:43:33,270 --> 00:43:34,310
Help me!
帮帮我

553
00:43:52,370 --> 00:43:55,040
Come here! Let's go.
过来  我们走

554
00:43:57,170 --> 00:43:59,340
Come on! Straight on!
过来  正前方

555
00:44:00,550 --> 00:44:02,550
-Come on! -Get them!
快  抓住他们

556
00:44:07,390 --> 00:44:09,060
Come on, get up!
快  起来

557
00:44:23,990 --> 00:44:25,570
You were right.
你说的对

558
00:44:26,030 --> 00:44:27,240
Mo!

559
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:30,160
Gwin! -Meggie!
-葛文  -美琪

560
00:44:31,620 --> 00:44:32,660
Meggie!

561
00:44:32,870 --> 00:44:35,420
Look! Hold on! Hold on! Wait, hold on!
美琪

562
00:44:36,880 --> 00:44:38,040
Don't move!
别动

563
00:44:48,310 --> 00:44:49,760
Watch out!
当心

564
00:44:55,270 --> 00:44:56,520
Dustfinger!
脏手指

565
00:44:58,110 --> 00:44:59,610
Where are we going?
我们要去哪

566
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:07,120
Don't leave me!
别丢下我

567
00:45:09,950 --> 00:45:11,660
The prisoners!
囚犯们

568
00:45:12,120 --> 00:45:14,830
They're escaping!
他们逃了

569
00:45:20,880 --> 00:45:22,130
Run!
快跑

570
00:45:22,300 --> 00:45:23,760
Hurry, get in! Run, run!
快点  进去  跑

571
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:25,630
Get in, get in!
进去  进去

572
00:45:30,350 --> 00:45:32,350
Get the keys, hurry up! Take all the keys!
拿钥匙  快点  把所有的钥匙都拿上

573
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:34,520
Which one? The one with the nine!
哪一个  9号

574
00:45:35,140 --> 00:45:37,230
Wait, wait, wait, Gwin!
等等  葛文

575
00:45:38,480 --> 00:45:40,150
Come on, Gwin.
快来  葛文

576
00:45:40,320 --> 00:45:42,070
Come on! Okay, go, go!
快来  走走

577
00:45:53,750 --> 00:45:55,160
Hold on!
注意

578
00:46:01,630 --> 00:46:03,000
Watch out!
当心啊

579
00:46:18,690 --> 00:46:20,190
Still think you're dreaming?
还觉得自己在梦里吗

580
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:21,860
Well, what else could it be?
不然还能是什么

581
00:46:22,520 --> 00:46:23,900
We're flying.
我们在飞啊

582
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:28,530
Or is it the night flying past us?
还是夜晚在我们身边飞

583
00:46:32,530 --> 00:46:34,080
He lives in Alassio.
他住在阿拉西奥

584
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:35,580
Which way is that?
怎么走呢

585
00:46:35,750 --> 00:46:40,000
South. South? Can't you be more precise?
-南边 -南边 没有具体地址吗

586
00:47:03,230 --> 00:47:04,400
Beats a camel, huh?
比骆驼好玩吧

587
00:47:04,570 --> 00:47:05,650
Farid.

588
00:47:05,820 --> 00:47:07,400
Oh, hooligan.
法利德 你这个小流氓

589
00:47:07,570 --> 00:47:11,410
Farid, some clothes for you. You'll freeze to death otherwise.
法利德  这些衣服给你  不然冻死你

590
00:47:11,570 --> 00:47:12,910
Apparently this is the place.
显然就是这里

591
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:16,370
Man in the fishmonger's says he lives in an apartment over the square.
一个鱼贩说 他住在广场那端的一个公寓

592
00:47:16,540 --> 00:47:17,580
Good. Great.
好  好极了

593
00:47:18,370 --> 00:47:19,410
Oh, l'm not coming.
我就不一起去了

594
00:47:19,870 --> 00:47:22,920
What do you mean? You have to come, otherwise he won't believe me.
你什么意思  你必须一起去

595
00:47:23,090 --> 00:47:25,590
Oh, l don't know. You can be pretty persuasive.
否则他不会信我们的 不一定  你很有说服力

596
00:47:25,750 --> 00:47:27,550
Huh? -You talked me out of a book.
你把我从书里个呼唤出来了

597
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:30,090
The book is right here within our grasp--
书唾手可得了  而你

598
00:47:30,260 --> 00:47:31,760
You're afraid.
你在害怕

599
00:47:34,930 --> 00:47:36,760
You've never read Inkheart, have you?
你没看过《墨水心》对吗

600
00:47:37,270 --> 00:47:38,930
What's there to read?
还用读吗

601
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:43,440
l've lived it. Except for the end, and l've got no interest in that.
那就是我的生活  除了结局

602
00:47:43,610 --> 00:47:44,610
Well, why not?
我不喜欢结局

603
00:47:44,770 --> 00:47:47,190
Do you know the end of your story, Meggie?
为什么 你知道自己故事的解决吗  美琪

604
00:47:48,240 --> 00:47:50,440
No. And l suspect you wouldn't want to.
不知道吧  我猜你也不想知道

605
00:47:50,610 --> 00:47:54,570
lt'd be like turning to the last page of a mystery.
这就像谜底揭开的一刻

606
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:58,910
-Where's the fun in that? -Well, l think l know the end of my story.
乐趣都随之消失 我知道我故事的结局

607
00:47:59,910 --> 00:48:01,580
Hm? -l'm going home.
-是吗  -我要回家

608
00:48:01,920 --> 00:48:03,210
Why?
为什么

609
00:48:03,380 --> 00:48:05,630
l'm sorry. lt's just all too real for me.
很抱歉  但我难以接受这一切

610
00:48:05,790 --> 00:48:09,760
l prefer a story that has the good sense to stay on the page where it belongs.
我所需要的故事是 书上的故事  而不是现实中的

611
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:12,800
No, l have to get back to my poor, desecrated books.
我要回去收拾那些可怜的被毁掉的书籍

612
00:48:12,970 --> 00:48:14,840
l want to mend them, put them in order.
我要修补他们  让一切恢复秩序

613
00:48:15,010 --> 00:48:18,010
-l'll do that. Let me-- -Here's some money for you.
-我会负责  让我  -这些钱是给你的

614
00:48:18,180 --> 00:48:20,520
You see, l've already bought my ticket.
看  我已经买好票了

615
00:48:21,140 --> 00:48:22,520
Goodbye.
再见

616
00:48:22,980 --> 00:48:24,440
Good luck.
祝你们好运

617
00:48:32,820 --> 00:48:33,820
-Elinor-- -Let her go.
-爱丽诺  -让她走吧

618
00:48:33,990 --> 00:48:35,110
Don't catch cold.
当心着凉了

619
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:36,820
Bye, then.
再见了

620
00:48:44,750 --> 00:48:46,670
Here it is. This must be it.
就是这了  肯定没错

621
00:48:47,340 --> 00:48:48,750
That's it.
到了

622
00:48:49,380 --> 00:48:51,300
What? Oh.
什么

623
00:48:53,840 --> 00:48:56,010
-Signor Fenoglio? -Yes?
-西格诺・费洛格里欧先生吗  -是的

624
00:48:56,850 --> 00:48:58,890
Sir, my name's Mortimer Folchart.
先生  我是莫提玛・弗夏特

625
00:48:59,060 --> 00:49:00,220
-l'm Meggie. -My daughter.
-我是美琪  -我的女儿

626
00:49:00,390 --> 00:49:02,520
-l want to be a writer too. -You do?
-我也想成为一名作家  -我知道

627
00:49:02,680 --> 00:49:06,650
Yes. Give me something to write with. Be quick, l've got a cake in the oven.
得有些东西  我才好签名啊 动作快  我蛋糕还在烤炉里呢

628
00:49:07,980 --> 00:49:09,730
You look like you've been taxidermied.
别像瓷娃娃似的傻站着啊

629
00:49:09,900 --> 00:49:12,780
-lf you want an autograph, give me a pen. -We don't want one.
-如果想要签名  给我笔  -我们不是来要签名

630
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:14,700
-You don't want an autograph? -No.
-你们不是为了签名  -不是

631
00:49:14,860 --> 00:49:17,490
Then why in the name of Chaucer's beard are you ringing?
那活见鬼了  你们按我门铃做什么呢

632
00:49:17,660 --> 00:49:19,280
Well....

633
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:23,040
Dustfinger's in the piazza, we just escaped from Capricorn's village...
脏手指在广场上 我们刚从摩羯的监狱里逃出来

634
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:25,620
...and you won't even believe what Basta tried to do.
你一定想不到巴斯达想干什么

635
00:49:27,710 --> 00:49:29,040
What?
什么

636
00:50:04,450 --> 00:50:05,500
Come home.
回家吧

637
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:09,130
Please, come home.
回来  求你了

638
00:50:09,790 --> 00:50:11,340
A good story, l'll give you that.
一个好故事  我说真的

639
00:50:11,500 --> 00:50:15,880
Silvertongues is a wonderful concept. Wish l thought of it. Too absurd to take seriously.
银舌头是个不错的词  我怎么没想到呢 这荒谬的难以置信

640
00:50:16,050 --> 00:50:20,050
l know my characters are so believable that they seem to leap off the page.
我知道我描绘的人物栩栩如生 一切的跃然纸上

641
00:50:20,220 --> 00:50:22,350
But it's simply not possible.
但这不可能啊

642
00:50:31,610 --> 00:50:34,230
Exactly as l imagined him.
和我想象的一模一样

643
00:50:49,000 --> 00:50:51,630
This must be what it feels like to give birth.
孕育生命一定也是这种感觉

644
00:50:52,130 --> 00:50:54,300
Wait, where you going? He doesn't want to meet.
等等  你去哪里  他不想见你

645
00:50:54,460 --> 00:50:57,300
Of course he does. l'm practically his father.
他肯定想  我实际上就像他父亲

646
00:50:57,470 --> 00:50:59,430
Well, what was that at the end?
这个究竟是什么

647
00:51:00,590 --> 00:51:01,890
lt's called Dragon's Breath.
这叫做龙之息

648
00:51:02,800 --> 00:51:04,600
You can teach to me?
你能教我吗

649
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:11,770
l'm sure that this must be very exciting for you to meet your characters.
我知道你 亲眼见到自己写的人物非常兴奋

650
00:51:11,940 --> 00:51:15,070
But the purpose that we came here was to find a way...
但我们来这儿找你是想

651
00:51:15,230 --> 00:51:16,820
...to get him back in the book.
让他回到书里去

652
00:51:16,990 --> 00:51:19,240
Your father's given me an idea for a character.
你父亲刚给了我人物的灵感

653
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:21,820
A master thief who steals things...
一个盗贼元凶

654
00:51:21,990 --> 00:51:25,490
...the way a blue jay swipes shiny objects off window sills.
通过念故事把我的人物都召唤出来

655
00:51:25,660 --> 00:51:27,330
l am not trying to steal them.
我不是想偷他们

656
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:31,670
You snatched them. You're trying to keep them from me. That, my friend, is thievery.
你从书中读出他们  从我这里拿走的 这个  叫做偷

657
00:51:31,830 --> 00:51:33,670
l'm just trying to get my wife back.
我只是想让我妻子能回来

658
00:51:34,670 --> 00:51:35,670
Dustfinger.
脏手指

659
00:51:35,840 --> 00:51:38,300
-So wonderful to meet you. -Oh, no, no. No.
-见到你真高兴  -不不不

660
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:41,180
The scars are perfect. As hideous as l imagined.
伤疤很完美  正如我想象的一样丑陋吓人

661
00:51:41,340 --> 00:51:44,470
l told you, he's afraid. But, oh, not me, l hope.
我告诉你  是他害怕了  不是我

662
00:51:44,850 --> 00:51:47,180
He's afraid of what happens at the end of the book.
他怕回到书中之后结尾那些事情就会发生

663
00:51:47,350 --> 00:51:49,020
What do you mean? Because he dies?
什么意思  他死了吗

664
00:51:50,190 --> 00:51:51,690
Oh, no.
不是

665
00:51:53,060 --> 00:51:56,440
-Oh, l see. Right, l'm sorry. -He dies in the end?
-我知道了  对不起  -他最后死了吗

666
00:51:56,610 --> 00:52:00,400
l had to make the story exciting, it's my job. They can't all have happy endings.
我要把故事写的很生动  这是我的工作 不能全都是完美的结局

667
00:52:00,570 --> 00:52:02,700
Life doesn't always, after all.
生活不是这样的  毕竟

668
00:52:05,410 --> 00:52:06,490
How's it happen?
他怎么死的?

669
00:52:06,660 --> 00:52:10,540
You're killed by one of Capricorn's men while trying to save Gwin.
当他救葛文的时候被摩羯的一个手下杀了

670
00:52:11,040 --> 00:52:14,210
lt's a very touching death scene. l cried when l wrote it.
很令人感动的情景  我写的时候都哭了

671
00:52:14,710 --> 00:52:17,170
You think l care what you wrote?
你觉得我在乎你写的什么吗

672
00:52:18,710 --> 00:52:22,050
You don't control my fate. Otherwise l wouldn't be here.
你主宰不了我的命运  否则我就不会在这儿了

673
00:52:22,220 --> 00:52:24,970
l'm not just some character in your book...
我不仅仅是你书里的人物了

674
00:52:25,140 --> 00:52:27,640
...and you...
你

675
00:52:27,810 --> 00:52:29,680
...you're not my god.
你也不是我的主宰

676
